### SECTION 1: AUTHENTICATION MIDDLEWARE TESTS
### Tests for valid/invalid token scenarios
### ===================================

### 1.1 GET Health Check (NO AUTHENTICATION REQUIRED)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1.2 GET All Users with VALID Bearer Token (SHOULD PASS)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

### 1.3 GET All Users with INVALID Bearer Token (SHOULD FAIL - 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{invalidBearerToken}}

### 1.4 GET All Users with NO Token (SHOULD FAIL - 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

### 1.5 GET All Users with VALID API Key (SHOULD PASS)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
X-API-Key: {{validApiKey}}

### 1.6 GET All Users with INVALID API Key (SHOULD FAIL - 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
X-API-Key: {{invalidApiKey}}

### 1.7 GET Specific User with Valid Bearer Token (SHOULD PASS)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

### 1.8 GET Specific User with MISSING Token (SHOULD FAIL - 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1

