### SECTION 2: REQUEST LOGGING VERIFICATION
### Tests to verify request/response logging is working
### ===================================

### 2.1 Simple GET request to verify logging captures method and path
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

### 2.2 POST request to verify logging captures method and success status
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "LogTest",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "logtest@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Test Engineer",
  "department": "QA",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2.3 PUT request to verify logging captures update operations
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Updated",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "john.doe@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Senior Engineer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2022-01-15",
  "isActive": true
}

### 2.4 DELETE request to verify logging captures delete operations
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/5
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

