### SECTION 3: ERROR HANDLING MIDDLEWARE TESTS
### Tests for exception handling and consistent error responses
### ===================================

### 3.1 GET Non-existent User (SHOULD RETURN 404 in standardized format)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/99999
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

### 3.2 POST with Invalid Email Format (SHOULD RETURN 400 in standardized format)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Invalid",
  "lastName": "Email",
  "email": "not-a-valid-email",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3.3 POST with Future HireDate (SHOULD RETURN 400 with detailed errors)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Future",
  "lastName": "Employee",
  "email": "future@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2099-12-31",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3.4 POST with Multiple Validation Errors (SHOULD RETURN comprehensive error list)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "   ",
  "lastName": "   ",
  "email": "invalid-email",
  "jobTitle": "",
  "department": "",
  "hireDate": "2099-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3.5 PUT Non-existent User (SHOULD RETURN 404 with friendly message)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/99999
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Ghost",
  "lastName": "User",
  "email": "ghost@example.com",
  "jobTitle": "Developer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-01-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 3.6 DELETE Non-existent User (SHOULD RETURN 404 with friendly message)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/99999
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

---

### SECTION 4: AUTHENTICATION EDGE CASES
### ===================================

### 4.1 Missing Authorization Header (SHOULD RETURN 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

### 4.2 Empty Bearer Token (SHOULD RETURN 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer

### 4.3 Malformed Bearer Token (SHOULD RETURN 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: Bearer123

### 4.4 Mixed Case X-API-Key Header (SHOULD PASS - case sensitivity check)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
x-api-key: {{validApiKey}}

### 4.5 Wrong Header Format (SHOULD RETURN 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: Basic dXNlcm5hbWU6cGFzc3dvcmQ=

---

### SECTION 5: AUTHENTICATED CRUD OPERATIONS
### Full CRUD tests with proper authentication
### ===================================

### 5.1 Create User with Bearer Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Authenticated",
  "lastName": "Creation",
  "email": "auth.create@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Software Engineer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2023-06-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 5.2 Create User with API Key
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users
X-API-Key: {{validApiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "ApiKey",
  "lastName": "Created",
  "email": "apikey.create@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "QA Engineer",
  "department": "QA",
  "hireDate": "2023-07-01",
  "isActive": true
}

### 5.3 Read All Users with Bearer Token
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

### 5.4 Read Specific User with API Key
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
X-API-Key: {{validApiKey}}

### 5.5 Update User with Bearer Token
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/1
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Lead Software Engineer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "hireDate": "2022-01-15",
  "isActive": true
}

### 5.6 Update User with API Key
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/2
X-API-Key: {{validApiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Jane",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@techhive.com",
  "jobTitle": "Senior HR Manager",
  "department": "Human Resources",
  "hireDate": "2021-06-20",
  "isActive": true
}

### 5.7 Delete User with Bearer Token
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/5
Authorization: {{validBearerToken}}

